\f1\b0\fs44 \cf0 Make the cocktails: In a glass pitcher, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/muddle/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 muddle}} the raspberries and jalapeno, then fill halfway with ice. Add the tequila, grapefruit juice, lime juice and agave. Take a second pitcher (the same size) and pour one into the other repeatedly to mix the drink together. Top it off with club soda or lemon-lime soda.\
Make the grapefruit salt: Crush the salt and grapefruit zest together with a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mortar-and-pestle/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mortar and pestle}}, then spread on a plate. Run a lime wedge around the rim of each glass, then dip the glasses in the grapefruit salt. Fill with the cocktails.}